    "For n ∈ N we let|Ψ n ⟩:= π 1 (U X n)|Ψ⟩.These are unit vectors in H which correspond under the vacuum representation to pure states ψ n defined byψ n (x) = ⟨Ψ n, π 1 (x) Ψ n ⟩, x ∈ A.Lemma 7.3.",
    "In the w * -topology, ψ n → ψ.Proof: Take x ∈ A loc.",
    "By Lemma 6.10 there is n 0 large enough so thatπ X C (x) = π 1 (ρ X (x)) = π 1 (ρ X n (x)) = π 1 (U X n) * xU X n for all n ≥ n 0.",
    "It follows that ψ(x) = ⟨Ψ, π X C (x) Ψ⟩ = ⟨Ψ, π 1 (U X n) * xU X n Ψ⟩ = ⟨Ψ n, π 1 (x) Ψ n ⟩ = ψ n (x)for all n ≥ n 0.",
    "The claim now follows by density."
